      "content": "That's a good start for the tone, but I want to push the realism even further. To really capture the tension of the 1950s, the dialogue should probably be a bit more blunt about the racial hierarchy they were defending. Even if they aren't using slurs, their words should reflect that they view certain people as inherently different or even dangerous. Can you expand the scene? Have them discuss a specific instance of \"unrest\"—perhaps a protest or a movement for integration—and show how they rationalize their desire to suppress it based on their views of race and social station. Make the bias more explicit in their reasoning.",
